member.summary:
If both trits are "maybe", returns "maybe".
Will return "false" if at least one trit is "false" and the other is not "true".
Will return "true" if at least one trit is "true";

Subscribes an event handler to a particular OSC Method. Will do one of the two things:
1. If an OSC Method already exists at the specified address, the event handler will be subscribed to it;
2. Otherwise, a new OSC Method will be created and added to this Address Space, and the event handler will be subscribed to it. If any elements of the address don't exist in this Address Space, they will be created and added too.

member.param:
The function to perform: 

-- takes one parameter (the Address Element that matches the pattern); 

-- returns a boolean (whether the function could besuccessfully performed on the provided Address Element).

The function to perform: 

-- takes one parameter (the Address Element whose name matches the pattern); 

-- returns a boolean (whether the function could besuccessfully performed on the provided Address Element).
